commit.message: Bump version and fix includeantruntime warning
Convert CHANGES to CHANGELOG.md and bump version

Merge pull request #9 from jcestibariz/master

Add support for Java 8 constants

Add support for Java 8 constants

Created from patch provided by @iloveeclipse, but only with significant
changes.
Better description of the test target
Profiling counting classes (with the help of the Harness and YourKit) and speeding it up by 15x. With a one line change.
Correcting mask for high bits when reading an u2 index.
Moving the example class to the data dir and copying it when compiling tests to be able to load the files when testing.

Correcting the problem reported by Tim Drury causing 'illegal constant pool index' problem. The problem was simply due to a byte whose high bit was set, thus making it a negative byte, which then got widened to a negative int.
Adding annotation parsing. Spec 4.18.15 of the Class File Format (Java 5).
One more BufferedInputStream optimization, thanks to Luke Usherwood.
Use a BufferedInputStream for optimization. Luke Usherwood reports this change reduces the processing time in his project from 33 seconds to 13 seconds.
